com.nokia.dempsy.config
Class ClusterDefinition

java.lang.Object
  com.nokia.dempsy.config.ClusterDefinition

public class ClusterDefinition
extends Object

A ClusterDefinition is part of an ApplicationDefinition. For a full description of the ClusterDefinition please see the ApplicationDefinition documentation.

Note: for ease of use when configuring by hand (not using a dependency injection framework like Spring or Guice) all "setters" (all 'mutators' in general) return the ClusterDefinition itself for the purpose of chaining.

ClusterDefinition

public ClusterDefinition(String clusterName)
Create a ClusterDefinition from a cluster name. A ClusterDefinition is to be embedded in an ApplicationDefinition so it only needs to cluster name and not the entire ClusterId.

ClusterDefinition

public ClusterDefinition(String clusterName,
                         Adaptor adaptor)

Create a ClusterDefinition from a cluster name. A ClusterDefinition is to be embedded in an ApplicationDefinition so it only needs to cluster name and not the entire ClusterId.

This Cluster will represent an Adaptor cluster. Use this constructor from a dependency injection framework supporting constructor injection.
